    <mj-section background-color="#ffffff"> 
      <mj-column>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="
              font-size: 20px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important; 
            ">1. US-China tariff wars</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">
           Donald Trump has <a href="https://news.harvard.edu/gazette/story/2024/12/how-china-tariffs-could-backfire-on-u-s/" target="_blank">warned China</a> of a 25% tariff on imports and an additional 10% levy unless China stops fentanyl from entering the US, a claim Beijing denies. These tariffs could disrupt global trade, increase costs, and create economic uncertainty. <a href="https://jackson.yale.edu/news/in-the-us-china-trade-war-how-did-some-bystander-countries-come-out-ahead/" target="_blank">Emerging economies</a> relying on US-China trade are particularly vulnerable to reduced demand and currency instability. Tariffs on technology could deepen the <a href="https://www.orfonline.org/expert-speak/the-great-u-s-china-tech-decoupling" target="_blank">global tech divide</a>, stalling innovation. Americans spent over $1 trillion on imports from China, Canada, and Mexico in 2024.
        </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>


    <!-- Content sections -->
 
    <mj-section css-class="mj_section" background-color="#ffffff">
      <mj-column>
      <mj-spacer height="0px" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="             
              font-size: 20px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important;">2. Middle East Tensions</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">The <a href="https://www.france24.com/en/middle-east/20241229-look-back-2024-retrospective-year-war-upheaval-middle-east-syria-gaza-assad-lebanon" target="_blank">Israel-Iran</a> conflict continues, with ceasefire attempts failing. Israel remains engaged in strikes on Iran, Syria, and Gaza. Syria’s interim government, following Assad’s ousting, plans to <a href="https://www.iranintl.com/en/202412254184" target="_blank">demand $300 billion</a> in compensation from Iran for military support to Assad’s regime. The region faces heightened risks of expanded conflicts and humanitarian crises.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>

    <mj-section css-class="mj_section" background-color="#ffffff">
      <mj-column>
      <mj-spacer height="0px" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="             
              font-size: 20px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important;">3. Increased oil production</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">Oil prices, slightly rising due to <a href="https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/markets/commodities/news/oil-holds-at-2-week-high-as-russia-iran-tensions-support-prices/articleshow/115640649.cms?from=mdr" target="_blank">sanctions</a> on Russia and Iran, could fall below <a href="https://www.marketwatch.com/story/oil-may-collapse-below-50-a-barrel-in-2025-if-this-perfect-storm-hits-the-market-87d72b8b" target="_blank">$50 a barrel</a> in 2025. Conflict-driven production increases in Russia and Iran may further reduce prices, disrupting energy markets. While lower prices benefit importing nations, instability could deter investments in energy infrastructure.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>

    <mj-section css-class="mj_section" background-color="#ffffff">
      <mj-column>
      <mj-spacer height="0px" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="             
              font-size: 20px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important;">4. Rogue AI from China</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">China’s <a href="https://time.com/6963787/china-influence-operations-artificial-intelligence-cyber-threats-microsoft/" target="_blank">rogue AI activities</a> include cyber espionage, disinformation campaigns, and economic disruption. Examples include <a href="https://www.npr.org/2023/12/13/1219080681/fake-social-media-accounts-are-targeting-taiwans-presidential-election" target="_blank">fake political endorsements</a> in Taiwan, <a href="https://www.npr.org/2023/09/28/1202110410/how-rumors-and-conspiracy-theories-got-in-the-way-of-mauis-fire-recovery#:~:text=After%20the%20wildfires%20in%20Lahaina,weapons%20to%20start%20the%20fire." target="_blank">misinformation</a> on US involvement in Hawaii wildfires, and claims of Japan’s <a href="https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-66667291" target="_blank">mishandling</a> of nuclear wastewater. Media literacy remains low globally, worsening the spread of AI-driven misinformation.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>

    <mj-section css-class="mj_section" background-color="#ffffff">
      <mj-column>
      <mj-spacer height="0px" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="             
              font-size: 20px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important;">5. Population decline</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4; filter: blur(5px)">Countries like Japan and South Korea face significant population decline, with South Korea declaring a <a href="https://www.newsweek.com/japan-south-korea-face-population-decline-1910371" target="_blank">national emergency</a> due to low fertility rates for the fourth consecutive year. As young people emigrate to wealthier EU nations, <a href="https://sciencebusiness.net/news/research-and-innovation-gap/shrinking-populations-are-increasing-brain-drain-woes-widening" target="_blank">Eastern Europe</a>, including Bulgaria, Latvia, and Croatia, is also affected by brain drain.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>

    <mj-section css-class="mj_section" background-color="#ffffff">
      <mj-column>
      <mj-spacer height="0px" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="             
              font-size: 20px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important;">6. Hostility towards immigrants in the West</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4; filter: blur(5px)"><a href="https://www.business-standard.com/finance/personal-finance/go-back-hostility-towards-immigrants-grows-in-us-france-ireland-canada-124121300773_1.html" target="_blank">Anti-immigrant sentiment</a> persists in the West, with immigrants blamed for economic struggles, job competition, and resource strain. Younger generations in Europe increasingly support <a href="https://www.politico.eu/article/far-right-europe-young-voters-election-2024-foreigners-out-generation-france-germany/" target="_blank">anti-immigrant parties</a>. Xenophobia spreads rapidly on <a href="https://lac.iom.int/en/blogs/social-networks-migration-xenophobia-what-discussion-region" target="_blank">social media</a>, and inadequate integration programs exacerbate the issue.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>

    <mj-section css-class="mj_section" background-color="#ffffff">
      <mj-column>
      <mj-spacer height="0px" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="             
              font-size: 20px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important;">7. Political polarization</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4; filter: blur(5px)">The 2024 elections saw populist and right-wing parties <a href="https://www.pewresearch.org/global/2024/12/11/global-elections-in-2024-what-we-learned-in-a-year-of-political-disruption/#polarized-battles-over-tradition-and-change" target="_blank">gain strength</a> globally. Far-right parties <a href="https://www.euronews.com/my-europe/2024/12/24/european-political-landscape-shifts-right-in-2024-as-far-right-gains-ground" target="_blank">dominated Europe</a>, while Donald Trump narrowly won the U.S. presidency. Frustration with traditional parties and political systems drove these shifts, highlighting cultural divides and demands for new leadership.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>

    <mj-section css-class="mj_section" background-color="#ffffff">
      <mj-column>
      <mj-spacer height="0px" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="             
              font-size: 20px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important;">8. Public health risks of lack of vaccines</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4; filter: blur(5px)">Conflicts and <a href="https://www.politico.com/news/2023/09/24/anti-vaxxers-political-power-00116527" target="_blank">vaccine hesitancy</a> are creating global public health risks. Many children in conflict zones like Gaza <a href="https://www.who.int/news/item/16-08-2024-humanitarian-pauses-vital-for-critical-polio-vaccination-campaign-in-the-gaza-strip" target="_blank">miss vaccinations</a>, while misinformation in the U.S. and Europe fuels hesitancy. Rising measles cases in the US and missed vaccines in war zones could spark future health crises.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>

    <mj-section css-class="mj_section" background-color="#ffffff">
      <mj-column>
      <mj-spacer height="0px" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="             
              font-size: 20px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important;">9. Suez Canal problems</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4; filter: blur(5px)">The Suez Canal <a href="https://uk.finance.yahoo.com/news/factbox-suez-disruption-inflation-risk-153600957.html?guccounter=1&guce_referrer=aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZ29vZ2xlLmNvbS8&guce_referrer_sig=AQAAALVPa1UEh66vJvMbu1CwDtQymMKMiPE7uq1sVVSXNjZJSRt2Aqe6UEVg-A146GZAMPAr11B4efh6ZauWNGSY6Mdml0GHHNgQIJLpKhkxr1N9mxUV169C33Qgysrcsu7rlUDX6ZIhcqbKFA83UObLYs2ywKb4kMCUiWrGkFkQNcB1" target="_blank">faces risks</a> from regional conflicts, terrorism, and environmental factors like droughts and overuse of resources. <a href="https://www.al-monitor.com/originals/2024/07/houthi-attacks-red-sea-shipping-wipe-2b-suez-canal-annual-revenue" target="_blank">Houthi attacks</a> have caused $2 billion in damages and alternative trade routes. <a href="https://unctad.org/publication/navigating-troubled-waters-impact-global-trade-disruption-shipping-routes-red-sea-black#:~:text=Red%20Sea%20and%20Suez%20Canals,as%20Ethiopia%20and%20the%20Sudan." target="_blank">Economic shifts</a> like slower trade or competition from alternative routes like the Northern Sea Route could reduce traffic. The canal’s aging infrastructure adds to its vulnerabilities.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>

    <mj-section css-class="mj_section" background-color="#ffffff">
      <mj-column>
      <mj-spacer height="0px" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="             
              font-size: 20px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important;">10. Chip shortages</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4; filter: blur(5px)"><a href="https://www.bain.com/insights/prepare-for-the-coming-ai-chip-shortage-tech-report-2024/" target="_blank">Global chip shortages</a> persist due to AI-driven demand for GPUs (graphics processing units) used in data centers and semiconductors, worsened by China’s control over key materials. China produces <a href="https://www.iss.europa.eu/publications/briefs/curbing-chinas-legacy-chip-clout-reevaluating-eu-strategy" target="_blank">30% of global legacy chips</a>, which puts other countries at risk of economic security and market distortion. Extreme weather, geopolitical tensions, and trade restrictions further strain supply chains, impacting industries reliant on advanced technology.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
